This paper deals with logical formalisms for describing dependencies between data, which is a topic that is relevant to several areas of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on Modal Team Logic, which is a generalization of Classical Modal Logic. The paper discusses the Uniform Interpolation Property, which is a property of logical systems that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence, machine learning, and automated reasoning. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
